Use `create_labels_if_missing: true` for new status/dropdown labels.

## Key Queries

```graphql
# List boards
query { boards(limit: 25) { id name columns { id title type } groups { id title } items_count } }

# Get items with pagination
query ($id: [ID!]!) { boards(ids: $id) { items_page(limit: 50) { cursor items { id name column_values { id type text value } } } } }

# Create item
mutation ($bid: ID!, $name: String!, $cv: JSON!) { create_item(board_id: $bid, item_name: $name, column_values: $cv) { id } }

# Update columns
mutation ($bid: ID!, $iid: ID!, $cv: JSON!) { change_multiple_column_values(board_id: $bid, item_id: $iid, column_values: $cv) { id } }
```

## Best Practices

1. Get board structure before modifying items
2. Always use GraphQL variables (never string interpolation)
3. Batch column updates with `change_multiple_column_values`
4. Paginate large item lists with cursor
5. Request only needed fields (reduces complexity cost)

